{"title_page": "Sampoorna Kranti Express", "text_new": "\n\n\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}}\n{{Infobox rail service\n| name =  Sampoorna Kranti Express<br /> \u0938\u0902\u092a\u0942\u0930\u094d\u0923 \u0915\u094d\u0930\u093e\u0902\u0924\u093f \u090f\u0915\u094d\u0938\u092a\u094d\u0930\u0947\u0938 \n| image   = Sampoornakexp.jpg\n| caption = \n| type = [[Superfast Mail/Express|Superfast]]\n| locale = [[Bihar]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[Delhi]]\n| first = 17 February 2002\n| last =\n| operator = [[East Central Railway Zone (India)|East Central Railway]]\n| ridership =\n| start = [[Rajendra Nagar Terminal]]'''(RJPB)'''\n| stops = 4\n| end = [[New Delhi Railway Station]]'''(NDLS)'''\n| distance = {{convert|1002|km|abbr=on}}\n| journey time = \n| frequency =  Daily\n| class = AC 1 Tier (01), AC 2 Tier (02), AC 3 Tier (03), Sleeper 3 Tier (09), Unreserved\n| seating (05)= Yes Pantry Car (01) EOG (02) (Total=22 Coaches)\n| sleeping = Yes\n| autorack = Not Available\n| catering = Yes\n| observation = Large Windows\n| entertainment = \n| baggage = Below the seats\n| otherfacilities=\n| stock = LHB Coaches\n| gauge = {{RailGauge|1676mm|allk=on}}\n| el =\n| train number = 12393UP / 12394DN \n| speed = {{convert|130|km/h|abbr=on}} top speed with halts<ref name=\"skranti\"/>\n| map =\n| map_state =\n}}The '''Sampoorna Kranti Express''' is an [[India]]n express passenger train service, which runs between [[Rajendranagar Terminal|Rajendra Nagar]] [[Patna]] and [[New Delhi]].The service began running on 17 February 2002 and is one of the fastest train services in India, traversing the 1002&nbsp;km distance in under fourteen hours, which puts it with likes of Patna, Dibrugarh, Tripura, Howarh Rajdhanis' It is faster than the previous [[Magadh Express]] Patna-New Delhi service and the [[Vikramshila Express]], [[Shramjeevi express]] on the same route.This train is also known as \"Janta ki Rajdhani\" as its fare is less than that of Rajdhani but matches it in speed and punctuality. It is quicker than few premier rajdhani trains on DDU-NDLS section.  \n\nSampoorna Kranti Express is also currently the fastest train in the Superfast category of Indian Railways. The train makes only three stops between Patna and New Delhi: at [[Kanpur Central]], [[Mirzapur]] and [[Mughalsarai, Varanasi|Mughalsarai]](also known as [[Pt. Deen Dayal Upadhyaya Junction  ]]). The train is hauled by [[WAP4 Engine|WAP7 Engine]]. It has LHB coaches. It is now operated on HOG system (Hotel Load) in which the power to coaches is provided directly from locomotive instead of EOGs (Power Cars). It is the first superfast train in India to have a LHB Rake. During its run with ICF coaches it ran with the maximum length permitted in Indian Railway of 24 coaches. Now, with LHB Coaches the composition of the train carriages is as follows:\nclass = AC 1 Tier (01), AC 2 Tier (02), AC 3 Tier (03), Sleeper 3 Tier (09), Unreserved seating (03) Pantry Car (01) EOG (02) (Total=22 Coaches). It is among the top priority trains of Indian Railways and does speeds of 130&nbsp;km/hour<ref name=\"skranti\">{{cite web | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/City/Patna/Sampoorna-Kranti-Exp-to-run-at-130-kmph/articleshow/36363824.cms | title=Sampoorna Kranti Exp to run at 130 kmph | publisher=[[The Times of India]], Patna | date=11 June 2014 | accessdate=11 June 2014 | author=Kumod Verma,TNN}}</ref> from 8 August 2015.\n\nThis Train Has Got Many Firsts To Its Name-\n\n* 1st Non AC Superfast train to get LHB coaches.\n* 1st Non AC Superfast train to run at a maximum speed of 130 km/h. \n*\n* 1st Non AC Superfast ICF Train to run at a maximum speed of 115 km/h as opposed to 110 km/h.\n\n==Traction==\nThis train hauled by [[WAP 7]] of [[Kanpur]](CNB) or [[Ghaziabad]](GZB) based locomotive end to end.\n\n==Time Table==\n<blockquote>\n= '''From [[Patna]] to [[Delhi]]- 12393'''. The train starts from [[Rajendranagar Terminal]] daily =\n</blockquote>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#FFD700\" | Station Code\n!! style=\"background-color:#FFD700\" | Station Name\n!! style=\"background-color:#FFD700\" | Arrival\n!! style=\"background-color:#FFD700\" | Departure\n!! style=\"background-color:#FFD700\" | Platform\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | RJPB\n| valign=\"top\" | [[Rajendranagar Terminal]]\n| valign=\"top\" | Starting Station\n| valign=\"top\" | 17:35 \n| valign=\"top\" | 2\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | PNBE\n| valign=\"top\" | [[Patna Junction]]\n| valign=\"top\" | 17:50\n| valign=\"top\" | 18:00\n| valign=\"top\" | 4\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | DDU\n| valign=\"top\" | [[Pt. Deen Dayal Upadhyaya Junction ]](formarly known as [[Mughalsarai Junction railway station  ]])\n| valign=\"top\" | 22:04\n| valign=\"top\" | 22:32\n| valign=\"top\" | N/A\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | MZP\n| valign=\"top\" | [[Mirzapur railway station]]\n| valign=\"top\" | 23:24\n| valign=\"top\" | 23:25\n| valign=\"top\" | 3\n|- \n| Valign=\"top\" | CNB\n| valign=\"top\" | [[Kanpur Central railway station|Kanpur Central]]\n| valign=\"top\" | 02:30\n| valign=\"top\" | 02:35\n| valign=\"top\" | N/A\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | NDLS\n| valign=\"top\" | [[New Delhi]]\n| valign=\"top\" | 7:50\n| valign=\"top\" | Destination Station\n| valign=\"top\" | 15\n|}\n\n'''From [[Delhi]] to [[Patna]] - 12394'''. The train starts from [[New Delhi Railway Station]] daily.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#FFD700\" | Station Code\n!! style=\"background-color:#FFD700\" | Station Name\n!! style=\"background-color:#FFD700\" | Arrival\n!! style=\"background-color:#FFD700\" | Departure\n!! style=\"background-color:#FFD700\" | Platform\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | NDLS\n| valign=\"top\" | [[New Delhi railway station]]\n| valign=\"top\" | Starting Station\n| valign=\"top\" | 17:25\n| valign=\"top\" | 16\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | CNB\n| valign=\"top\" | [[Kanpur Central railway station|Kanpur Central]]\n| valign=\"top\" | 22:25\n| valign=\"top\" | 22:33\n| valign=\"top\" | N/A\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | MZP\n| valign=\"top\" | [[Mirzapur railway station]] \n| valign=\"top\" | 01:40\n| valign=\"top\" | 01:41\n| valign=\"top\" | 2\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | DDU\n| valign=\"top\" | [[Pt. Deen Dayal Upadhyaya Junction]] (formarly known as [[Mughalsarai Junction railway station ]])\n| valign=\"top\" | 03:30\n| valign=\"top\" | 03:40\n| valign=\"top\" | N/A\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | PNBE\n| valign=\"top\" | [[Patna Junction]] \n| valign=\"top\" | 06:55\n| valign=\"top\" | 07:05\n| valign=\"top\" | 4\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | RJPB\n| valign=\"top\" | [[Rajendranagar Terminal]]\n| valign=\"top\" | 07:35\n| valign=\"top\" | Destination Station\n| valign=\"top\" | 2\n|}\n\n===In News===\n01. It was in news recently over extension to Madhupur, Jharkhand after the demand came from Member of Parliament Shri Nishikant Dubey of Godda constituency, Jharkhand . The news of extension led to widespread protest by Passenger Association and Railfans and criticism from seven member of Parliament from Bihar. Eventually the extension plan was dropped after such amount of criticism. \n\n\n\n<br />\n\n* \n*[[Sanghamithra Express]]\n*[[Bagmati Express]]\n*[[List of named passenger trains of India]]\n*[[Indian Railways - Travel Coach types and their seating / berths]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n{{Railways in Bihar}}\n{{Railways in Northern India}}\n{{Railway lines in Eastern India}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sampoorna Kranti Express}}\n[[Category:Transport in Patna]]\n[[Category:Transport in Delhi]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in Bihar]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in Uttar Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in Delhi]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in Rajasthan]]\n[[Category:Railway services introduced in 2002]]\n[[Category:Express trains in India]]\n\n\n{{India-rail-transport-stub}}\n", "text_old": "\n\n\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}}\n{{Infobox rail service\n| name =  Sampoorna Kranti Express<br /> \u0938\u0902\u092a\u0942\u0930\u094d\u0923 \u0915\u094d\u0930\u093e\u0902\u0924\u093f \u090f\u0915\u094d\u0938\u092a\u094d\u0930\u0947\u0938 \n| image   = Sampoornakexp.jpg\n| caption = \n| type = [[Superfast Mail/Express|Superfast]]\n| locale = [[Bihar]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[Delhi]]\n| first = 17 February 2002\n| last =\n| operator = [[East Central Railway Zone (India)|East Central Railway]]\n| ridership =\n| start = [[Rajendra Nagar Terminal]]'''(RJPB)'''\n| stops = 4\n| end = [[New Delhi Railway Station]]'''(NDLS)'''\n| distance = {{convert|1002|km|abbr=on}}\n| journey time = \n| frequency =  Daily\n| class = AC 1 Tier (01), AC 2 Tier (02), AC 3 Tier (03), Sleeper 3 Tier (09), Unreserved\n| seating (05)= Yes Pantry Car (01) EOG (02) (Total=22 Coaches)\n| sleeping = Yes\n| autorack = Not Available\n| catering = Yes\n| observation = Large Windows\n| entertainment = \n| baggage = Below the seats\n| otherfacilities=\n| stock = LHB Coaches\n| gauge = {{RailGauge|1676mm|allk=on}}\n| el =\n| train number = 12393UP / 12394DN \n| speed = {{convert|130|km/h|abbr=on}} top speed with halts<ref name=\"skranti\"/>\n| map =\n| map_state =\n}}The '''Sampoorna Kranti Express''' is an [[India]]n express passenger train service, which runs between [[Rajendranagar Terminal|Rajendra Nagar]] [[Patna]] and [[New Delhi]].The service began running on 17 February 2002 and is one of the fastest train services in India, traversing the 1002&nbsp;km distance in under fourteen hours, which puts it with likes of Patna, Dibrugarh, Tripura, Howarh Rajdhanis' It is faster than the previous [[Magadh Express]] Patna-New Delhi service and the [[Vikramshila Express]], [[Shramjeevi express]] on the same route.This train is also known as \"Janta ki Rajdhani\" as its fare is less than that of Rajdhani but matches it in speed and punctuality. \n\nSampoorna Kranti Express is currently the fastest train in the Superfast category of Indian Railways. The train makes only three stops between Patna and New Delhi: at [[Kanpur Central]], [[Mirzapur]] and [[Mughalsarai, Varanasi|Mughalsarai]](also known as [[Pt. Deen Dayal Upadhyaya Junction  ]]). The train is hauled by [[WAP4 Engine|WAP7 Engine]]. It has LHB coaches. It is now operated on HOG system (Hotel Load) in which the power to coaches is provided directly from locomotive instead of EOGs (Power Cars). It is the first superfast train in India to have a LHB Rake. During its run with ICF coaches it ran with the maximum length permitted in Indian Railway of 24 coaches. Now, with LHB Coaches the composition of the train carriages is as follows:\nclass = AC 1 Tier (01), AC 2 Tier (02), AC 3 Tier (03), Sleeper 3 Tier (09), Unreserved seating (03) Pantry Car (01) EOG (02) (Total=22 Coaches). It is among the top priority trains of Indian Railways and does speeds of 130&nbsp;km/hour<ref name=\"skranti\">{{cite web | url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/City/Patna/Sampoorna-Kranti-Exp-to-run-at-130-kmph/articleshow/36363824.cms | title=Sampoorna Kranti Exp to run at 130 kmph | publisher=[[The Times of India]], Patna | date=11 June 2014 | accessdate=11 June 2014 | author=Kumod Verma,TNN}}</ref> from 8 August 2015.\n\nThis Train Has Got Many Firsts To Its Name-\n\n* 1st Non AC Superfast train to get LHB coaches.\n* 1st Non AC Superfast train to run at a maximum speed of 130 km/h. \n*\n* 1st Non AC Superfast ICF Train to run at a maximum speed of 115 km/h as opposed to 110 km/h.\n\n==Traction==\nThis train hauled by [[WAP 7]] of [[Kanpur]](CNB) or [[Ghaziabad]](GZB) based locomotive end to end.\n\n==Time Table==\n<blockquote>\n= '''From [[Patna]] to [[Delhi]]- 12393'''. The train starts from [[Rajendranagar Terminal]] daily =\n</blockquote>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#FFD700\" | Station Code\n!! style=\"background-color:#FFD700\" | Station Name\n!! style=\"background-color:#FFD700\" | Arrival\n!! style=\"background-color:#FFD700\" | Departure\n!! style=\"background-color:#FFD700\" | Platform\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" | RJPB